partlex: 1. Used at the beginning or end of a sentence or immediately next to a verb to mean the action took place the week before the week of speaking. English = last week, one week ago.

2. Used at the beginning or end of a sentence or immediately next to a verb to mean the action took place the week before an already specified week in the past. English = the previous week, one week before that.
nomlex: 1. The calendar week before the week of speaking. English = last week, one week ago.
2. The calendar week before an already specified week in the past. English = the week before that, the previous week.
